name: Necrophilia Canyon
description:
Introduction

NOTE: Just recently saw that hikers that have gone in there from the bottom and the top are calling this canyon "Big Fall Canyon". And this is one of the canyons where I found illegal bolts drilled into the wall for anchors, but no trip report about it. Maybe the illegal bolts placements keep them for getting it out there.

Approach

THE OTHER PHOTO I UPLOADED, THAT IS WITHIN THIS CANYON PHOTO FILE SECTION, WAS TAKEN LOOKING BACK AT THE CANYON AFTER WE HAD DESCENDED IT. THEN WE WERE ON THE WAY UP TO DO OUR NEXT CANYON PLANNED. AND THAT CANYON WAS POTHOLE CANYON. A VERY UNIQUE VANTAGE POINT THAT YOU CANNOT SEE FROM ANYWHERE ELSE. AND QUITE AN IMPRESSIVE VIEW OF THIS CANYON

Descent

this canyon has one spectacular 140' rappel, and two smaller drops. A long way to go there for such limited technical activity. But the canyon still is a very spectacular place to visit, and still a worthy place for canyoneers, even with it's limited technical action.

Exit

Red tape
